description:
Correctly handle SPDY GOAWAY frames.

Committed: https://src.chromium.org/viewvc/chrome?view=rev&revision=195032

messages.text: I'm going to let akalin handle this instead :) Let me know if you'd prefer me for any reason. I'll skim though.

> I'm going to let akalin handle this instead :) Let me know if you'd prefer

finished. :)

looks mostly good, a few comments

https://codereview.chromium.org/14232014/diff/1/net/spdy/spdy_session.cc
File net/spdy/spdy_session.cc (right):

https://codereview.chromium.org/14232014/diff/1/net/spdy/spdy_session.cc#newcode1146
net/spdy/spdy_session.cc:1146: ActiveStreamMap new_active_streams;
Curious -- are we worried about re-entrancy here? If not, seems easier to use lower_bound to find the first stream > last_good_stream_id and start deleting from there

add a comment for CloseAllStreamsAfter? Perhaps document the additional stuff CloseAllStreams does over CloseAllStreamsAfter(0, _)

unfortunately, deque::erase is O(n). Can you do something similar to RemovePendingWritesForStream where you keep track of *out_it and then delete everything after that? May want to copy that loop above and replace the conditional. I don't know if it's worth decomping out into a helper method.

Before I got started?  I think we were doing something like:

abandoned_streams.Add(active_streams_.size());

At least that was the state when I started hacking.  Looks like the name of that var changed in a recent CL.
